title: People over Profit: Billionaires Shouldn’t Rule America
description:
## **People over Profit: Billionaires Shouldn’t Rule America**

The United States is not a corporation, and our government is not a for-profit enterprise. Elon Musk is not a government official. He’s a billionaire with no accountability to the American people, and nobody voted for him. Our democracy deserves better.

Musk and Trump will only be defeated by a massive, bipartisan movement of everyday Americans standing up against corruption, authoritarianism, and huge tax breaks for the rich, while fighting for the programs that working people need.

** This is a BIPARTISAN, PEACEFUL Protest** 
**No violence or Destruction of Property will be tolerated** 

**The People over Profit Movement**

Right now, millions of Americans across the political divide are struggling. 60% live paycheck to paycheck, many earn very low wages, and 85 million lack proper health insurance. College is too expensive for young people, a quarter of seniors live on $15,000 a year or less, and childhood poverty is among the highest in the world. We also face a severe shortage of affordable housing.

At the same time, the wealthiest Americans, like Elon Musk, Jeff Bezos, and Mark Zuckerberg, are getting richer. Since Trump’s election, their combined wealth has grown by over $200 billion—more than the bottom half of the country. Meanwhile, the middle class shrinks, and democracy is at risk.

Our goal is to protect democracy and create an economy that works for everyone, not just the rich. As the wealthiest country in the world, we have the potential to use new technologies to improve everyone’s lives, but instead, most of the wealth goes to the people who need it the least.

We must make healthcare a human right, raise wages to a living standard, improve public education, address the housing crisis, create good-paying jobs to fight climate change, and end all forms of discrimination.

**We the People believe that in the richest country in the history of the world we must establish that:**

1. Healthcare is a human right and must be available to all regardless of income.

2. Every worker in America is entitled to earn a decent income. We must raise the minimum wage to a living wage and make it easier for workers to join unions.

3. We must have the best public educational system in the world, from childcare to vocational training, to graduate school – available to all.

4. We must address the housing crisis and build the millions of units of low-income and affordable housing that we desperately need.

5. We must create millions of good paying jobs as we lead the world in combating the existential threat of climate change.

6. We must abolish all forms of bigotry.

description:
## It’s time to end the health care crisis. Join the National Day of Action for Single Payer! Saturday, May 31st 1pm-3pm.

Our health care system is broken—and it’s **killing** us. For-profit insurers and corporate middlemen deny care, drive up costs, and profit off our pain. Decades of piecemeal reforms have only made things worse: skyrocketing prices, massive waste, and some of the worst health outcomes among wealthy countries.

**We say: enough.**

### We demand a system that puts people before profit—where health care is treated as a human right, not a business.

#### We are calling for:

- The elimination of private insurance companies and for-profit care.

- A national, publicly funded single payer program that covers everyone—comprehensively and equitably.

- A transformation of our health care system to serve communities, not corporations—freeing caregivers from corporate control and putting power in the hands of the people.

This event is happening in Portland, but we’re not stopping here. Activists are organizing sister actions across Oregon—from the coast to the high desert. Stay tuned for more info on how to plug in near you!

On the **National Day of Action**, people across the country—patients, nurses, union members, small business owners, neighbors and organizers—will take to the streets to demand real change. This is about building a mass movement to take profit out of care and put National Single Payer on the political agenda—now.

Bring your families (kid friendly!), neighbors, friends, everyone you know and join us to turn collective outrage into collective action: put National Single Payer on the nation’s agenda!

We need continuous coverage on Tuesday, May 20, 2025, for the Primary Election at the Board of Elections until all votes have been counted. 

Volunteers MUST be registered Democrats from Lancaster County. You will be volunteering within the Board of Elections offices at 150 N. Queen St.  We need coverage all day from 8 am - 11 pm or until all ballots are counted.

Training information will be shared prior to the Primary.

title: Juneteenth Block Party!
description:
🎉 Brookline’s Juneteenth Chitlin’ Circuit Block Party 🎶
Presented by Brookline for the Culture & the Town of Brookline

Date: Wednesday, June 19, 2025
Time: 12:00 PM - 6:00 PM
Location: 345 Harvard St (with a special closure of Stedman Street for the party!)

Step back into history and dance into the future at this year’s Juneteenth celebration — inspired by the legendary Chitlin’ Circuit!

The Chitlin’ Circuit was a powerful network of Black-owned venues that gave rise to some of the most iconic voices in American music — from Bessie Smith and Ella Fitzgerald to James Brown and Little Richard. This Juneteenth, we’re paying homage to those trailblazers with live music, soul food, fashion, storytelling, and community celebration.

This event isn’t just a block party — it’s a living history lesson, a cultural festival, and a powerful reminder of Black resilience and creative brilliance. Join us for:

✨ Live performances & DJ sets honoring the music of the Chitlin’ Circuit
✨ Vibrant Black-owned vendor marketplace
✨ Community art installations & storytelling spaces
✨ Soul food and fusion cuisine from local chefs
✨ Line dancing, two-stepping, and electric slides all day!
✨ Family-friendly games & activities

Why It Matters:
Juneteenth is not just a holiday — it’s a call to action to remember our ancestors’ fight for freedom, to celebrate Black culture in all its beauty, and to continue the fight for justice today. This year, we’re adding the spirit of the Chitlin’ Circuit to that legacy — showcasing how Black music, art, and community thrived despite systemic exclusion.

Wear Your Red, White & Blue
Juneteenth’s traditional colors symbolize the resilience and enduring hope of Black Americans — so show up and show out in your boldest red, white, and blue looks!

FREE & OPEN TO ALL
Want to volunteer, sponsor, or table? Contact us at brooklinefortheculture@gmail.com

Let’s make history together — see you there!
#BrooklineJuneteenth #ChitlinCircuit #BlackCultureMatters #Juneteenth2025
